"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بَرَّأَ","root":"برأ","pos":"V","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2416"]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to create, to bring into being","examples":[{"text":"مَا أَصَابَ مِن مُّصِيبَةٍ فِي الْأَرْضِ وَلَا فِي أَنْفُسِكُمْ إِلَّا فِي كِتَابٍ مِّن قَبْلِ أَن نَّبْرَأَهَا","english":"No disaster strikes upon the earth or among yourselves except that it is in a register before we bring it into being."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to absolve, pardon, exonerate","examples":[{"text":"يَا أَيُّهَا ٱلَّذِينَ آمَنُوا لَا تَكُونُوا كَٱلَّذِينَ آذَوْا مُوسَى فَبَرَّأَهُ ٱللَّهُ مِمَّا قَالُوا"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"It is grouped at the root ب ر ء (b r ʔ), but borrowed from Classical Syriac ܒܪܳܐ (braʾ, “to create”). In Syriac the same root is more widespread, whereas in Arabic it is exotic – the verb appears in the Qurʾān in its finite form only in 57:22, and three times in the active participle form."},"ipa":["/ba.ra.ʔa/"]}